<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 01 at 5:12PM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Lake
and northern Ashtabula Counties through 600 PM EDT...
At 510 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Madison, or near Geneva-On-The-Lake, moving northeast at 30 mph.
These storms continue to track near the lakeshore.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Ashtabula, Conneaut, Geneva-On-The-Lake, Geneva, Madison, North
Kingsville, Perry, Kingsville, North Perry, Edgewood, Plymouth Center
and North Madison.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
